    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-01-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-01-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="973"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d973">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 5, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>889. Your 1400, January 4. As message appears to be partially in code, the
                    Department would be pleased to forward it after being put <pb facs="0956"
                        n="698" xml:id="pg_698"/> in plain, commercial language. Bring this to early
                    attention of <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Sir Edward Grey</persName> to have
                    little delay as possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
